Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.60,0:19:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the information is processed right\Nthrough your spiritual understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.00,0:19:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which releases endorphins instead of\Nadrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He balances his acupuncture system,\Nstrengthens the thymus gland, increases
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.48,0:19:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of circulating killer cells,\Nwhich increases immunity to disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that builds up the neurotransmitters in\Nthe brain
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.03,0:19:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually end up\Nparalyzed anyway in bliss,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which which beats suicide. Anyway,\NSo there is, you see, because we set
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.36,0:20:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,goals for ourself. We read the spiritual\Nliterature and we set goals for oursel
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we think, well, we're not there yet.\NSo we put oursel down, etc., etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.60,0:20:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nnot realizing that all along we are on a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.91,0:20:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,different path. So never get discouraged\Non the spiritual pathway because you are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.91,0:20:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on the pathway.\NIt's better to be discouraged on the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.96,0:20:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual pathway\Nthan in temporary euphoria on the other
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.60,0:20:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway.\NThe temporary high that you get from
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.48,0:20:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,adrenaline. Yeah.\NYeah. Substitute for endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.36,0:20:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I never didn't intend to speak\Nabout this this morning until near the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.55,0:20:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,end, but I thought it's so important.\NI'll put it in in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll get it back to it in the\Nend in pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.79,0:21:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right? Because this is a spiritually\Noriented group of such a high
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.55,0:21:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration, we can say things that we\Ncan't say elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.32,0:21:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,without being thought mad\Nor labeled a mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.32,0:21:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\None technically is a mystic to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.44,0:21:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of God as the self as the\Ninnate sense of I the universalness of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.79,0:21:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the essence of the mystic\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,about which I have to do something some\Nkind of work for next month anyway Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.03,0:22:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The way we've tried to describe really\Nwe've avoided the whole subject of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.72,0:22:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,religion.\NWe draw from the ranks of all religions
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.00,0:22:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and incorporate the essential truth of\Nall religions
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.24,0:22:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same same time avoid them. avoid\Nthem
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.36,0:22:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for specific reasons.\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.03,0:22:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,one's spiritual awareness\Nshould really not depend on the say so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.12,0:22:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of authorities\Nor supposed authorities,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.76,0:22:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ecclesiastic authorities\Nof anybody anywhere in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.96,0:22:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of the truth of spiritual\Nreality
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.79,0:22:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has only one source and that's yourself.\NThe external can verify it, but it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.20,0:23:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,substitute for the real.\NTherefore, in the books I do and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.08,0:23:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures,\NI don't try to give any authority to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.48,0:23:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what I say by quoting from elsewhere.\NIf elsewhere was successful, we wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.15,0:23:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all be here.\NNo, elsewhere has not been successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.88,0:23:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe difficulty is it gets stuck in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.44,0:23:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,authoritarianism.\NAuthoritarianism
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.15,0:23:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and one begins to quote out there.\NPlus, all the religions have arisen in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.44,0:23:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ethnic situations,\Ngeographic situations,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.15,0:23:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've become layered with\Nhistorical events and personages
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.32,0:24:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and ecclesiastic languaging,\Napproval by higher authorities,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.15,0:24:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, subservience to ecclesiastic\Nauthority,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.55,0:24:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is a great deterrence.\NThe spiritual reality described
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.79,0:24:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout time has always been the\Nsame.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.55,0:24:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In a week or two, I I ran across\Nthe experience described here in these
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.40,0:24:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures within\Nto all myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.03,0:24:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally read it somewhere. You\Nnever read theods. I looked over the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.36,0:24:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,planishads and there was somebody who\Nfinally got it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.84,0:25:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they got it right. Oh, wow.\NWell, he got it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.52,0:25:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The undoing of the ego, then the\Ndisassembling of the ego is what we've
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.48,0:25:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,really been talking about. How to\Nunderstand the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.20,0:25:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Each level of consciousness is unique in\Nto itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.27,0:25:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one has its own specific\Ncharacteristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.72,0:25:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk about very advanced levels of\Nconsciousness, but today we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.20,0:25:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,do a whole slide on the levels in the\N200s and 300s
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.27,0:25:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the critical line.\NOnce you're over the line, the rest is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.96,0:25:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,certain. The real trick is getting over\Nthe line. And we find that spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.84,0:25:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,attributes which calibrate maybe 250 or\Nsomething
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.40,0:26:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if you persist in them will take you\Nrapidly up the scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.88,0:26:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How many have not been here before?\NOh dear. Oh dear. Oh dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.12,0:26:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. We're going to rapidly\Nrecapitulate the earlier lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.76,0:26:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing will be left out that you need\Nto know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.00,0:26:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We all start the lectures at the same\Nunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.88,0:26:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulties of with an audience\Nlike this which is in the 400s, many of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.96,0:26:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you in the high 400s.\NThe big barrier is the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.40,0:26:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Rare is the person who gets beyond\Ncalibrated level 499. Huh? And so the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.03,0:26:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,first thing we want to disassemble\Nis the worship of the intellect and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.36,0:27:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,reason and logic\Nto a group like this. Reason and logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.08,0:27:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligence and education is the\Nleading light of their life. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.48,0:27:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it then becomes the very limitation to\Ntranscending it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.96,0:27:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first thing we need to do is to\Ndisassemble
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.52,0:27:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that major structure called the\Nintellect
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.84,0:27:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a formidable strength.\NThe intellect out of which has come
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.55,0:27:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,science and the great wonders of this\Nworld is formidable and quite powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.52,0:27:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been capable of curing most of the\Ndiseases I treated when I was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.12,0:27:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,at a hospital for infectious diseases\Netc. Almost all those diseases are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.08,0:27:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So the 400s are extremely powerful. The\Nworld of science invention,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.91,0:28:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of reality, the\Ndifferential calculus, the the computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.36,0:28:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the space age, all comes out of the\N400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.88,0:28:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s then become the limitation as\Nwe see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.20,0:28:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein 499, Freud 499.\NSir Isaac Newton 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s then become the barrier to the\N500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.24,0:28:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, we've got a pointer. Right there.\N>> Right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.08,0:28:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Isn't that grand? Just like in the\Nmovies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.20,0:28:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. All right. So, for those who\Nhaven't been here before, we have Cal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who hasn't read Power versus\NAll right. So, I don't want to get too
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.08,0:28:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,rudimentary.\NWhat we discovered is you can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.84,0:29:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the levels of consciousness. We created\Na scale logarithmic one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.84,0:29:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We found everything that makes you go\Nweak. We
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.44,0:29:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you go weak. We calibrated that.\NIt ended up at 200. Below 200 makes you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.24,0:29:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak. Over 200 makes you go strong.\NIt's based on the kinesiologic response
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.15,0:29:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the reaction of consciousness\Nas life to truth or the absence thereof.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.27,0:29:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it is not a yes or a no. It's\Na yes or a not yes. The universe cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.96,0:29:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,answer no. It either responds or does\Nnot respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.48,0:29:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while somebody will write me a\Nletter. Couldn't we create an electronic
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.91,0:29:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,wonder computer machine that would do\Nkinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.52,0:29:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thereby missing the whole point.\NThe whole point is it's the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.96,0:30:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness that is answering.\NYou could do that with a computer if it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.67,0:30:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you could turn it into a human being.\NSo the it's the response of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.15,0:30:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a difficult concept. All of\Nprotoplasm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.67,0:30:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is open to and responds positively to\Nthat which is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.52,0:30:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,true life and it tends to recoil from\Nthat which is not life. The other
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.32,0:30:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,strange thing about consciousness is\Nthat it's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.15,0:30:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a giant electromagnetic field\Nof in which you participate in which
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.27,0:30:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your consciousness participates\Nat varying levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.44,0:30:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all levels of consciousness.\NWe see that from here up to once you get
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.39,0:30:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,over the level of integrity profound\Nchanges happen. Therefore it's in that's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.60,0:30:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the most important step. People worry,\N"How high is my calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.24,0:31:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness?" You don't have to worry\Nabout that. As long as you're over 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.39,0:31:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you got nothing to worry about. You just\Nkeep doing what you're doing and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.44,0:31:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually you get there. That's all.\NImpatience. You have to let go
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.44,0:31:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,impatience. I want enlightenment. I want\Nit now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.64,0:31:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, you don't want it now. You\Nthink you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.52,0:31:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You think bad life was bad before. Wait.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.64,0:31:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Took me\N30 years to talk about it or write about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.08,0:31:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\N10 years to recover, I'd leave the world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.60,0:31:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and 10 years to recover so I could\Nfunction again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.15,0:31:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You need friends that know that you're\Nserious about spiritual work. I tell
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.44,0:31:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody, always have friends that you\Nknow know you are serious about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.51,0:31:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work.\NIn case you do just go into a sudden 600
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.84,0:31:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and you sit there sort of bliss bliss\Nout and the family wonders you've gone
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.44,0:31:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,crazy or you're catatonic and they call\Nin adopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.79,0:32:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So the\Npeople of a more advanced understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.48,0:32:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,able to understand abstraction\Nunderstanding reason meaningfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.12,0:32:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They see God as the infinite wisdom of\Nthe universe. the omnition, the sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.67,0:32:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the omniscience of God.\NBut that reason then becomes the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.12,0:32:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The block\Nthat was the block the height that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.15,0:32:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein ran into\Nat the SV conference in Copenhagen
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.79,0:32:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,1929\Nwhere all the great theoretical
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.55,0:32:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,physicists of the day mathematicians had\Ngathered
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.79,0:32:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Heisenberg principle is what he\Ncouldn't handle. The Heisenberg
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.03,0:32:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,principle introduced the realization\Nthat consciousness itself already
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.48,0:32:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,profoundly alters the state and\Ncondition of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.88,0:33:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nso
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.88,0:33:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the 400s what the fortress behind the\N400s is the belief in causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.24,0:33:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So we always start the lectures with\Ntrying to explain how things come about.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.51,0:33:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The illusion of causality is the biggest\Nblock to transcending the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.36,0:33:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The illusion of causality is profoundly\Nimportant to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.60,0:33:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the beginning of every\Nlecture, we try to explain how things
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.91,0:33:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,actually come about\Nbecause you begin to intuitit it. You
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.72,0:33:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to sense it.\NPrinciple of causality calibrates around
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.03,0:34:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,450 or 460.\N>> Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.08,0:34:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It calibrates over 450 over 460. 465.\NAll right. The principle of causality
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.39,0:34:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 460.\NThe theory of evolution, Darwin's theory
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.44,0:34:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of evolution, calibrates around 450,\N455.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.35,0:34:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Nyou can't really explain the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.59,0:34:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,including divinity, from a consciousness\Nlevel at 455
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.15,0:34:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,won't work.\NYou have to transcend the Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.80,0:34:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm of reality\Nwhich is based on the belief in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.35,0:34:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,causality\Nthat there's a this causing a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.80,0:34:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The pathway to enlightenment is\Nnondualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.04,0:34:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle of causality is inherently\Nand profoundly dualistic. So one can see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.56,0:35:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the mind to become\Nenlightened to realize the truth of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.64,0:35:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God within\Nit's necessary to transcend the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.64,0:35:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect.\NTherefore it's necessary to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.32,0:35:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the illusion of causality.\NSo long as you think there's a this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.80,0:35:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,causing a that you're stuck in duality.\NThe most profound duality that you get
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.59,0:35:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,stuck in is that there must be an\Nindependent separate personal eye that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.52,0:35:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is causing things out there.\NA separate eye, separate from the one,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.44,0:35:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,separate from the field, unique,\Nindividual, autonomous,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.64,0:35:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a little god entity.\NNobody wants to admit that the core of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.88,0:35:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,their ego wants to be God. But that's a\Nfact.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.20,0:35:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we reveal that truth?\NYes. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.92,0:36:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The core of egoentricity.\NAll right. Doesn't want to let go being
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.20,0:36:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in charge\Nconsiders it the self
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.68,0:36:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as the author.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.92,0:36:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it sees the ego sees the core of the ego\Nas
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.68,0:36:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of its life. It sees it as\Nsovereign
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.48,0:36:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will fight to the death to\Nmaintain its sovereignty
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.11,0:36:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,including sacrificing your physical\Nexistence. If you really threaten the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.16,0:36:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ego,\Nit will throw you over a cliff in an
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.56,0:36:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,instant\Nbecause it will survive. In this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.16,0:36:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality, it doesn't care anything\Nabout.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.44,0:36:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just another opportunity for\Nitself to be what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.11,0:36:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It will happily sacrifice itself to be\Nright. Everyday's headlines tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.72,0:36:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that people blow themselves up to be\Nright.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.44,0:37:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Or worse than that, they blow you up to\Nbe right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.28,0:37:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A busload of children will do. For\Nstarters,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.80,0:37:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that should get a war going for 50 years\Nor so. And it has, hasn't it then? That
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.35,0:37:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,one started with a blowing up a bus load\Nof children.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.96,0:37:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it knows how to trigger hatred.\NKnows all the tricks. The ego knows how
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.35,0:37:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive.\NIt is frightened to death of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.96,0:37:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Last thing wants is peace.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.92,0:37:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see how this how causality\Nhas to be replaced by a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.32,0:37:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding.\NEverything already is what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.07,0:37:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its prior karma.\NThe marble sitting there because the kid
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.32,0:37:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,put it on the pool table or whatever.\NYou know all events have coalesed now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.96,0:38:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,into\Na present state or condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.04,0:38:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything karmically inherits\Na potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.28,0:38:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,also a limitation.\NA strawberry plant cannot become a rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.35,0:38:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already destined.\NIt has a potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.83,0:38:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to move from the unmanifest\Nto the manifest which is the source of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.11,0:38:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,creation\Nis an aspect of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.56,0:38:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything then comes into existence\Nwith a potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.72,0:38:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality then becomes an actual\Nactuality
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.32,0:39:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if the field favors that. If it's\Nfavored by the climate and by the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.04,0:39:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions and by the field,\Nthere's no guarantee that the rose will
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.24,0:39:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,bloom at all. It has the potentiality.\NNothing can cause the rose to bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.52,0:39:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NIf conditions are favorable then its
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.20,0:39:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nis expressed in this domain as an
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.32,0:39:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality.\NYou see the potentiality then becoming
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.04,0:39:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,actualized.\NIf conditions are correct, if conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.24,0:39:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are favorable,\Nit comes into existence as it the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.80,0:39:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment of its potentiality\Nby virtue
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.24,0:40:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the power of the overall field.\NEverything exists within a field,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.59,0:40:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite field which is like a giant\Ngravitational field.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.88,0:40:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Every decision we make, every thought,\Nevery feeling first of all gets
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.00,0:40:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,registered forever in the field of\Nconsciousness. That's why we can
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.59,0:40:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,retrieve it with kinesiology.\NEvery decision
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.92,0:40:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if you look at your spirit karmic\Ncore of your spirit as a little iron
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.52,0:40:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,filing then every decision thought\Netc changes the charge on this little
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.59,0:40:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,filing more positive or more negative\Nthe field which is the power and the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.04,0:40:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God\Nis infinite infinitely powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.76,0:41:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful.\NIt doesn't do anything. Power stands
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.24,0:41:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there\Nlike a giant electromagnetic field like
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.11,0:41:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,like gravity. It just stands there. It\Ndoesn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.59,0:41:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity is not arbitrary. It has no\Nparts. It doesn't move from here to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.16,0:41:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NDoesn't have a solar plexus. Doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.35,0:41:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have emotions.\Nnot subject to human limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.48,0:41:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the ancient anthropomorphic\Nprojections of God do not calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.88,0:41:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely high.\NThe field gravity doesn't get angry at
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.68,0:41:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody.\NHe pushes over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.31,0:41:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God was angry at the Kleenex.\NNo, the response of the field is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.48,0:42:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute. The justice of God is\Ncontinuous,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.07,0:42:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,always present.\NJudgment day is always
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.07,0:42:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,judgment day is ongoing. Is this\Nalwaysness resist?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.83,0:42:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not then or then.\NNeither in the past nor in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.16,0:42:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing possible to be going on\Nis already going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.88,0:42:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The charge on your little iron filing\Nhas already put you in the field where
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.52,0:42:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,its charge automatically goes. It goes\Nas a consequence of its own potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.16,0:42:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the freedom of will, the\Ninfinite and profound freedom. One does
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.88,0:42:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not move anywhere in the universe except\Nby personal ascent. It's only by your
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.96,0:43:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,agreement\Nthat you move from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.20,0:43:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The other night on TV they were doing a\Nrerun of that profound hero in
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.28,0:43:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the war?\NWhat's where is the war? Where's the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.35,0:43:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,war?\N>> Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.04,0:43:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Iraq. Don't be timid. Yes, Iraq. I'm not\Ntoo left for this morning. Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.44,0:43:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't he a lawyer and detected an\Ninjured uh American lady? young slim
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.83,0:43:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,young little blonde lady\Nthat she was not only injured and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.07,0:43:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,tortured but being tortured as well\Nabused
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.07,0:43:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway heroic\Nwe have permission to ask this we have
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.92,0:43:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to ask this\Nhis karma I mean let's see his
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.76,0:44:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated level of consciousness jumped\Nover 200 250 300 holy Christ 350
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.72,0:44:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,one instant 350 jump of calibration of\Nlevel of consciousness this. So how long
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.04,0:44:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,does it take to move ahead in\Nconsciousness? One decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.72,0:44:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person advances five points\Nin a lifetime. One decision 350 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.24,0:44:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So the decision to sacrifice\Njeopardize his own life for the highest
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.44,0:44:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,good\Nout of love and service to love
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.59,0:44:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. was a profound move.\NProfound move. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.80,0:44:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Things come about then as a result as a\Nconsequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.40,0:44:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have a white board here today.\NAs a white as a con as a consequence of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.92,0:44:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the field\Nwe detect. You know when we were in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.11,0:45:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe I think someplace\Nthere was this space shuttle that uh
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.40,0:45:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's insulation fell off or something\Nand of course immediately they started
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.44,0:45:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to look for the guilty party but after\Nthorough investigation they came the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.16,0:45:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,closest to the truth that I've read in a\Nheadline in years says it was a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.11,0:45:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of the climate\Nthe climate of NASA or whatever the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.04,0:45:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,agency was the ambiance, the overall\Nclimate of it. Huh? So when the climate
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.64,0:45:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is correct, the potentiality to become a\Nrose blooms. You see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.48,0:45:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,things are not caused one.\NEverything comes into existence as the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.64,0:45:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of multi-millions of factors\Nall operating. And when they're
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.24,0:45:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,fortuitous, they cross a certain\Nthreshold.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.64,0:46:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Going from potentiality to actuality\Nmeans crossing a certain threshold.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.00,0:46:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When enough grains of sand are put on\Nit, it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.64,0:46:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhen there's enough snow on the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.07,0:46:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mountains of Colorado,\Nthe snow piles up, the temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.28,0:46:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,change, barometric pressure changes,\Nthere's the layer of ice, then a lot of
