Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.35,0:46:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,bigger and bigger and bigger and bigger\Nbased on what the incline is, what the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.80,0:46:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,weather is, the barometric pressure, and\N10 million other factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.04,0:46:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certain threshold point at\Nwhich
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.44,0:46:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,boom, the avalanche starts. Yeah. A\Nslight vibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.40,0:47:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Slight vibration.\NThe coyote yips. And that's what does it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.48,0:47:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all it needed. low frequency, you\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.64,0:47:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the skier says, "Golly\Nall sudden."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.04,0:47:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the skier cause the avalanche? No.\NThough every contributing factor then
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.96,0:47:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you see for every factor to even exist\Nrequires
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.48,0:47:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole universe throughout all of\Ntime
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.24,0:47:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the complexity and\Nmulti-billions and trillions
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.64,0:47:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,quadrillions there's numbers for big\Nwords I forget what they are big numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.96,0:47:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean use in advanced physics\Nanyway the number of factors is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.44,0:47:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,innumerable and And we found they're\Nactually infinite. The number of factors
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.72,0:47:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,required for any event to materialize to\Nactualize is actually infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.48,0:48:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So things then coalesce out of the field\Nlike a cloud appears in the sky. Its
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.20,0:48:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,design is not preset. Its potentiality\Nto become a cloud isn't even there. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.48,0:48:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not even a a little cloud becoming a big\Ncloud. It's a no cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.11,0:48:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of no cloudness arises\Nwhen a million factors are favorable
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.72,0:48:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,out of it coalleses out of the field\Ncomes into actuality within our domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.64,0:48:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore there is no cause of anything.\NThere is only everything fulfilling its
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.64,0:48:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic potential when the accumulated\Nconditions reach a certain threshold.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.96,0:48:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When the itch gets strong enough, you\Nscratch it. But not before it's strong
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.52,0:48:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,enough.\NAnd how come the mosquito bite got
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.00,0:48:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there? So to get an itchy mosquito bite,\Nyou see, takes all of the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.80,0:49:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,universe throughout all of time.\NIs that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.92,0:49:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is caused by I mean it's such a\Nsimplistic and I always say the exa the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.83,0:49:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,example of simplicity\Nis helotropism where the child says why
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.64,0:49:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,does the flower follow the sun and the\Nteacher says helotropism
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.48,0:49:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the child says oh he doesn't know\Nanything more than he knew before
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.44,0:49:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's the principle of causality\NBecause nothing is causing anything and
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.11,0:49:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore creation and evolution are one\Nand the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.52,0:49:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution is the sequential witnessing\Nof creation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.52,0:49:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and creation is continuous because\Ncreation is the continuous process
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.52,0:50:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the potential becoming the actual\Ncontinue. So creation is continuous and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.76,0:50:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ongoing.\NYou don't have to stand up every time
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.11,0:50:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a fact. Is it creation is\Ncontinuous and ongoing because the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.35,0:50:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God which is the powerful\Nfield out of which potentiality becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.04,0:50:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality is constantly present.\NThe power of God then is the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.44,0:50:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a field so powerful\Nthat the unmanifest becomes manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.07,0:50:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest\Nclassically called out of the Godhead
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.04,0:50:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,arises\Nthe unmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.80,0:50:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In Christianity called Godhead,\Nin Buddhism called the void, out of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.00,0:51:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,seeming nothingness arises everything\Nby virtue of the power of divine
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.83,0:51:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ordinance.\NNothing has the power within itself to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.24,0:51:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,create its own existence.\NEven the most radical
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.11,0:51:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific redemptionist is stuck\Nto explain the existence of all the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.92,0:51:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,things discussed including one's own\Nthoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.28,0:51:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we want to catch up the people who\Nare not that familiar with it. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.24,0:51:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated all the levels of\Nconsciousness. We discovered that they
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.83,0:51:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,correlate with common human experience.\NI can't use my finger anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.48,0:51:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to use this.\NThe consciousness levels below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.64,0:52:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Nthis is an evolutionary scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.76,0:52:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As you go up the scale, you see more\Nadvanced evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.52,0:52:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, life had a very\Ndifficult time to survive. In the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.20,0:52:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning, there was no animals here.\NThere was no advanced forms of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.31,0:52:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The most primitive form of life then to\Nsurvive. Let's say if you were going to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.48,0:52:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,create life on Mars,\Nit would have to be programmed to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.40,0:52:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,survive. So the energy of life as it\Nappears initially and throughout all the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.96,0:52:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,lowest forms is solely concerned with\Nme, myself, my survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.88,0:52:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not concerned about you. It\Ndoesn't even conceive of you unless
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.76,0:53:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you're edible.\NSo the core of the ego then is survival
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.55,0:53:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is thought to be the source of\None's life not realizing that it comes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.55,0:53:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,out of divinity. It thinks it's\Nself-created. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.00,0:53:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the source of life then becomes more\Nevolved. You see more and more evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.55,0:53:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,animals.\NYou start out with bacteria that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.48,0:53:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate at one.\NWe go up to insects. We'll do animals
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.48,0:53:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,later. But as you evolve through the\Nanimal kingdom, then finally you see the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.31,0:53:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,homminid. You see the early forms of pre\Nprehuman coagulan man who calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.72,0:53:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,around 75.\NAll the early forms of man, homo rectus
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.44,0:53:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates extremely low. It's not until\Nyou see homo sapiens. Homo sapiens with
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.52,0:53:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nfrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.04,0:54:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Homo sapien then didn't score very high\Neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.04,0:54:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the history of Europe and\Nthe early history of civilization, you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.31,0:54:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,see mankind was not too evolved anywhere\Nfrankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.96,0:54:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And only in the late 1980s did the\Nconsciousness level of mankind cross
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.31,0:54:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,over 200. It was at 190 all through the\Nmiddle ages, 1800s.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.88,0:54:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, we're in a new paradigm.\NAnd this new paradigm of reality, which
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.28,0:54:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 200, is spiritual\Nawareness. And we call it homospiritus.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.68,0:54:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Homospiritus because it now has a an\Netheric brain. And it now processes
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.20,0:54:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,things differently than any of his\Nhomminid predecessors.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.24,0:54:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. Homo spiritist is correct.\NHomo spiritist then appears
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.88,0:55:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and in future history books we could\Ndate it to 19 late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.64,0:55:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when the consciousness level became\Npredominantly positive
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.68,0:55:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and overruled the animal consciousness.\NAll the you look at the history of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.16,0:55:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe, it's nothing but\None tribe conquering another pack of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.52,0:55:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,wolves attacking another pack of wolves\Ntrying to take over its territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.88,0:55:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, they had no motivation or\Njustification at all. There's no
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.92,0:55:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,justification for any war in history\Nreally. We just wanted your land other
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.88,0:55:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,than greed. Solar plexus greed.\NSo you see the animal history is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.59,0:55:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but the animal acting itself out acting\Nout in human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.00,0:55:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Homo sapien then was a big advance over\Nhis predecessor because he had a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.48,0:55:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,cerebral cortex. The only difficulty was\Nthe animal in him was still predominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.76,0:56:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And to the animal, the cerebral cortex\Nis only a more clever, successful way of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.52,0:56:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,being an animal.\NThe fights on Monkey Island for
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.76,0:56:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,territory and mating privileges, etc.,\Ncontinued the same. But now
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.79,0:56:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal ego became really dangerous\Nbecause now it had a cerebral cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.11,0:56:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It could not only figure out how to tear\Nout your juggler vein, it could create
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.28,0:56:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,an atomic bomb to do it.\NWow. North Korea, various places were
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.68,0:56:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,scared of them because of\Nbecause of the power. because of the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.31,0:56:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,irrationality behind the power.\NNot the power, nuclear power,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.96,0:56:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but the finger on the trigger is not all\Nthere.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.96,0:56:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not all there upstairs. That's what we\Nworry about. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.64,0:57:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the difficulty then is now the\Nanimal was given tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.55,0:57:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you gave all the animals in\Nthe woods guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.24,0:57:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we did. That's what we did.\NWe gave all the animals guns. We went
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.76,0:57:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,into countries that the calibrated level\Nof consciousness is around 90. We gave
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.79,0:57:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,them all guns.\NWhat do you think consciousness level 90
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.04,0:57:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to do with a gun?\NIt's going to shoot you, idiot. What do
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.92,0:57:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you think he's going to do with it?\NWhat did they think they were going to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.07,0:57:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,do with it?\NFight on our side. Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.28,0:57:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Your side.\NLet's go on. So then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.00,0:57:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we see we don't have to make the ego\Nwrong. We have to see that the core of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.31,0:57:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego is the the remnant of the\Nanimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.76,0:57:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nthat's right. So this is what's left of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.83,0:58:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal and this is transcending the\Nanimal all the way to it. So this is to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.92,0:58:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,me to to me the emergence of homo\Nspiritus
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.83,0:58:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which became measurable in the late\N1980s when the consciousness level of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.24,0:58:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind jumped from 190 spectacularly to\N207. A huge jump. Not only is 17 points
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.96,0:58:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a huge jump but it passed over a\Ncritical line from destruction to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.79,0:58:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,construction.\NYes, we should go to the next. Okay. So
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.20,0:58:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we're we're just going back to\Nrecapitulate the whole thing how we did
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.20,0:58:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it. This is the distribution of levels\Nof consciousness in the mankind. In
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.20,0:58:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind we see that 85% of the world's\Npopulation is still predominantly at the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.31,0:58:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,effect of their animal nature.\NIf you're aware of that, you see it
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.59,0:59:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly. I have to is walk down the\Nstreets in a big city and you see
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.64,0:59:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,humanl looking animals.\NHang on to your billfold.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.20,0:59:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd this is uh Karen did this slide. She
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.04,0:59:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,did it originally in color, but I I\Ndidn't want to go into color shock, so I
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.35,0:59:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,made her go back to gray. So this is a\Ndifferent way of understanding it. The
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.31,0:59:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,power of the 15% is greater than the the\Nnumbers of the 85%.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.83,0:59:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As we go up the calibrated scale of\Nconsciousness, the power of
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.20,0:59:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness becomes so much more\Npowerful because those are logarithmic
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.68,0:59:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.04,0:59:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,here's another way she did it.\NUh this 15%
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.31,0:59:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalances the 85%.\Nthe rest of the world. Okay. So, the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.64,1:00:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of consciousness then has not\Nmoved since 19 the late 1980s. We all
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.72,1:00:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hoped that they would. It would resist.\NIt hasn't moved since the late 1980s.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.04,1:00:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. Mhm.\NAll right. So, it hasn't crossed a
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.28,1:00:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,certain threshold yet. Certain threshold\Nyet. Let's move on and see what is next.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.16,1:00:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.\NBecause of causality, because of this
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.40,1:00:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,causing a that, the mind thinks\Ndualistic. The animal mind thinks
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.48,1:00:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,dualistically. It thinks of a me here\Nand a rabbit there. And it has to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.28,1:00:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,measure the distance between the two. So\Nthe animal brain then is equipped to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.40,1:00:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,prey on others, etc. It has to divide\Nlife into me versus that. And usually
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.64,1:00:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's me versus lunch\Nand you are lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.48,1:00:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Political lunch when it gets more\Nsophisticated. Political lunch. And they
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.11,1:01:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,get out there and pontificate some of\Nthese politicians if they knew how we
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.31,1:01:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what I was calibrating. I think they\NI said, "Is this has he told any truth
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.59,1:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at all in the last 20 minutes?" And I\Nget no.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.76,1:01:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego loves to pontificate. It\Npontificates.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.52,1:01:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and it loves to be right.\NSo one of the sacrifices one has to make
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.64,1:01:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual work is the pleasure of\Nbeing right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.52,1:01:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One ends up being neutral.\NThe intellect says, "But isn't that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.92,1:01:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,being Nambi Pami?"\NYes, that's being powerfully Nandandy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.55,1:01:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Pami. Boy, you better watch out.\NThe pleasure of giving up the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.88,1:01:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,righteousness of being right is that you\Ndon't have the guilt of winning.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.92,1:01:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a big argument with your\Nspouse, your mother, somebody, and you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.68,1:02:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,walk away, I want, but you also are\Nguilty. Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.68,1:02:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so when you really don't care who wins,\NI feel that everybody, the other person
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.79,1:02:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,should always win, I tell them right off\Nthe bat, I agree with you. What? You
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.83,1:02:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,win.\NOh, he says
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.20,1:02:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fine with me if other people are\Nright and I'm wrong. It's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.48,1:02:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to get off the duality of the\Nego. So, first we dissolve causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.55,1:02:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is its real core.\NThen we begin to see out of its idea of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.07,1:02:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,causality. It splits everything\Ndualistically.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.35,1:02:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there is no duality in\Nreality. Duality is a projection of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.72,1:02:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,perception in which we set an arbitrary\Nline and say everything on this side is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.44,1:02:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right and everything on this side is\Nwrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.68,1:03:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I could say this end of the stick is\Nlong and this end of the stick is short
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.07,1:03:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is my point from which I'm\NI could go here and say well both ends
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.48,1:03:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are equal. Then I could go here and say,\N"No, the right end is longer than the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.55,1:03:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,left end. All I've changed is\Npositionality. The reality hasn't
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.92,1:03:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,changed at all."\NThat's what the intellect does
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.83,1:03:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly. And it's very fast at it,\Ntoo.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.92,1:03:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We can take it apart by showing that\Nthere is actually only one variable, not
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.16,1:03:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,two variables, one variable. Here we\Nhave the presence of heat or not heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.20,1:03:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat is either present or not present.\NWe call it hot and cold, but that's just
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.83,1:03:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,linguistic. There's no difference. Heat\Nis not the opposite of cold. Cold is the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.59,1:03:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,absence of heat. We can do the same\Nthing with desiraability. Desiraability
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.79,1:03:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or aesthetics.\NWe can do the same thing with goodness,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.72,1:04:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what we picture as heavenly, what we\Npicture as horrible, which is above or
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.28,1:04:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200. Generally\Nthe calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.68,1:04:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then are what you're really calibrating\Nis the evolution of consciousness. The
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.64,1:04:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of consciousness and while\Nit's still predominantly animal in
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.20,1:04:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,nature\Nit makes you go weak
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.59,1:04:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when it becomes concerned with others\Nand values and
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.96,1:04:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,higher concepts then it makes you go\Nstrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.35,1:04:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So light we see here there's no no\Nduality of light and darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.07,1:04:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only a lot of light or not any\Nlight. Lots and lots of light as light
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.03,1:04:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,goes away. So you don't have two\Nconditions. You don't have two
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.11,1:04:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,variables. You either have the presence\Nor the absence of light. Therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.55,1:04:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you have either the presence or the\Nabsence of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.55,1:05:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And the presence of love\Nis at the high end of the scale. And as
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.59,1:05:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to the bottom, there's the\Nabsence of love. The komodo dragon does
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.72,1:05:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not love you.\NDoes not love anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.00,1:05:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And to him, an ankle is food.\NNext,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.03,1:05:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal nature, as entertainers have\Nfound out, which I've warned people many
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.76,1:05:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,times.\NIn the end, the lion will eat you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.44,1:05:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Its intrinsic nature has not changed. In\Nthe end, the tiger will eat you. The
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.20,1:05:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lion will eat you. The komodo dragon\Nwill bite you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.20,1:05:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the naivee of the 500s. The naive\Nthis
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.79,1:05:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the na the blind side of the 500s\Nis its denial
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.20,1:06:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that the wild animal still is within the\Ntame animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.59,1:06:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in the 500s get blindsided.\NThey're easy to take. And the sharks
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.40,1:06:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,know that.\NThe sharks know that people in the five
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.88,1:06:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,high 500s saintly people don't see any\Nevil out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.92,1:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,think no there's no point to guard\Nagainst it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.59,1:06:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. You can trust everybody.\NNo, that's not the opening of the third
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.20,1:06:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,eye of the Buddhist body is discernment.\NThere are people
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.03,1:06:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you can love them and not give them your\Nmoney
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.79,1:06:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because they'll pad the bill.\NNow a naive person. So the 500s people
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.16,1:06:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to be naive.\NThey go into a a view of life in which
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.28,1:07:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,being other than the way they are see\Nlife is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.24,1:07:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get more advanced you realize\Nthat one takes into consideration the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.28,1:07:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,other possibility.\NOne is merely aware of it, cautious
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.31,1:07:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about it, but you no longer hate it or\Nfear it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.40,1:07:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't hate it. If somebody pads the\Nbill, so they pad the bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.03,1:07:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Go away therein. Okay.\NUh we said that the mind the other
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.68,1:07:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting thing we discovered this we\Nbrought forth considerably in the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.07,1:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures is that the mind is primarily\Nsilent.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.35,1:07:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As the ego dissolves and thinkingness\Ndisappears,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.28,1:07:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the most stunning thing that happens is\Nnot only the exquisite beauty and the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.83,1:07:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,revelation of the divinity of all that\Nexists
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.68,1:07:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the presence of a love of of\Ninfinite softness and yet infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.92,1:08:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,power.\NThe mind goes silent
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.88,1:08:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and one realizes that the mind is\Nactually silent at all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.00,1:08:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,98% of the mind is silent at all times.\NYou don't have to pay attention to your
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.55,1:08:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,chemical processes, your physiology.\NYou don't have to be like a centipede
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.12,1:08:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,deciding which leg to put after which.\N98% of it is done for you. You've only
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.31,1:08:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,got 2% left.\NHow does this 2% manage to survive? When
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.52,1:08:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,people to go to meditate they say my\Nmind keeps thinking thinking thinking I
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.27,1:08:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,can't make it stop.\NThis 2% then has certain certain modus
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.75,1:08:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,operandi.\N98% of your mind is silent at all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.92,1:08:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually 98% of your mind easily as you\Nlisten to me is already silent. You're
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.71,1:09:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,only listening to about 1% of your mind.\N98% is silent. It's like a huge field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.15,1:09:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,big silent field and over here there's a\Nlittle bit of something going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.04,1:09:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're focused on that little bit of\Nsomething that that's going on. And the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.44,1:09:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting thing is that that one or 2%\Nthat's thinking and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.00,1:09:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,mentalizing things uh you become\Nhypnotized by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.00,1:09:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,98% of the mind is silent.\NThat's let's just verify that is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.04,1:09:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,only 2% is operating\Nand the 2% has hypnotized you. So you've
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.56,1:09:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,like watched television so long that\Neven after it's off you're still looking
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.40,1:09:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at the screen.\NAnd here's its tricks. It politicizes,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.44,1:09:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,moralizes. This is everyday's newspaper.\NEvery night's news dramatizes,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.88,1:09:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophizes.\NYou find yourself not being in accord
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.36,1:10:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with\Ncommon humanity as it presents itself
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.92,1:10:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,via the news etc. If you begin to\Ntranscend this because the media do the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.76,1:10:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,same thing. They know this is how your\Nmind works.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.28,1:10:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some type gets run over by a truck.\NTypes get run over by trucks every day
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.19,1:10:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,folks everywhere in the world. Is that\Nnews? No.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.92,1:10:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could catastrophize it, dramatize\Nit, emotionalize it, and get the camera
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.60,1:10:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,right at the right image, I get the\Nmother blubbering and the poor little
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.40,1:10:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,dead baby there, I can get a sob out of\Neverybody, get indignant letters to the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.04,1:10:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,trucking company.\NShouldn't have been loud. We can
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.56,1:10:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,politicize it. We can moralize it. We\Ncan idealize how it should be. We can
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.15,1:10:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothesize what the government should\Nhave done.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.08,1:11:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We can criticize everybody in sight.\NEvery event, first two things happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.60,1:11:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's going to be the fall guy, right?\NAnd who do we sue?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.92,1:11:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First phone call the families make is\Nthrough their lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.52,1:11:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We romanticize, we criticize,\Nemotionalize, dramatize, catastrophize.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.67,1:11:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We theorize about how it should and\Ncould be. We rationalize it. We
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.84,1:11:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,fantasize. We infantalize everything.\NIt's like nobody, everybody in America
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.88,1:11:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,now is a infant, a neurotic infant.\NEverybody is made uncomfortable by
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.32,1:11:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,something.\NI'm made uncomfortable by people being
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.80,1:11:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomfortable.\NWe just got a a book of all the all the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.64,1:11:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,things you can't words you can't use in\Nthe books anymore, you know, by somebody
