Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.80,1:11:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't use anymore.\NWe're going to end up everything is
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.12,1:12:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be generic.\NWe'll all just be people. You can't be a
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.00,1:12:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,male people or female people. Can't be\Nyoung. Can't be old. Can't be from any
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.19,1:12:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,particular country. Can't be any color.\NCan't have any level of education. Can't
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.56,1:12:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have any disability. Can't There's\Nnothing you can say about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.88,1:12:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Blank person met blank person and\Nthey're dead blank.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.60,1:12:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,can even mention husband or wife. It's a\Nmarital person.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.67,1:12:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that's intellectualization. See, and
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.08,1:12:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it infantilizes people because in this\Nworld you got to learn how to take it,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.12,1:12:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,mentalize, idealize, glamorize, demonize\Nand predominantly victimize. Our whole
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.32,1:12:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,world is a world of\Nvictim perpetrator and victim which is a
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.12,1:12:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,complete projection from mentalization\Nnext slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.52,1:13:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was reviewing uh Karl Marx when I was\Nin London in Oxford
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.80,1:13:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the glaring uh the glaring error in\Nin Marxism is so stunning. You say how
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.08,1:13:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,could large populations and whole\Ncountries even fallen for it. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.60,1:13:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it instantly sees perpetrator\Nand victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.56,1:13:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you got a poor town. Company comes\Nin. They put spend their savings and
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.12,1:13:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they build a store. They start an\Nenterprise. Now all the people in this
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.64,1:13:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,little town got something to do. They\Nall got jobs and now they can buy cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.92,1:13:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The population gets bigger. They build a\Nhigh school.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.48,1:13:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They got prosperity. Now this company\Nthat came in and made this all possible
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.28,1:13:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is the perpetrator.\NThese are all now victims according to
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.12,1:13:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Markx\Nuh according to car marks. So that
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.15,1:13:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,dualizing things into perpetrator and\Nvictim then
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.00,1:13:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is misperceiving and projecting it onto\Nthe world. Instead of seeing them as a
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.67,1:14:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,benefactor, they see it as the\Nperpetrator. And now you've got the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.48,1:14:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,worker versus capitalism and all the\Ncrap that goes with it. All right. So
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.32,1:14:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about different universes.\NWe talked about the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.48,1:14:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the world of the ego which\Nthings are logical and progressive and
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.92,1:14:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,provable.\NAnd then now science has discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.76,1:14:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics and we discovered that\Nthings are quite disorderly
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.08,1:14:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're not predictable that\Nthey're sporadic
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.84,1:14:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore I use today the term\Nthreshold. The threshold is a composite
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.56,1:14:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of all things both predictable and\Nunpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.36,1:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All things knowable and unknowable\Nbecause the stochastic
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.32,1:14:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is unknowable. Unknowable.\NUnknowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.36,1:14:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the sky diver whose parachute\Ndoesn't open discovers that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.60,1:15:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,everything knowable has been checked\Nout.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.92,1:15:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But he forgot about the unknowable.\NThe unknowable arises just as you leave
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.36,1:15:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the plane. The unknown, undetectable,\None tiny flick in
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.19,1:15:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,one particular thought pattern in\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.19,1:15:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the difference between life\Nand death. the fact that
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.12,1:15:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the non-Newtonian subjective\Nmatrix of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.28,1:15:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,things are not predictable\Nis why
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.71,1:15:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pushing one's luck with extreme sports\Nis
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.36,1:15:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of course you don't really have to keep\Nthis body you can have another one
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.60,1:15:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll go on to the next one next one\Nthese are just recapitul ulations and
